	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)">Office of <persName>ALLEN &#38; CO.</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>82 BEAVER STREET</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>NEW YORK</placeName>&#44; <date>Apl 24 1865</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear sir and friend.</p>
				<p>You gave me Bill for Books<lb/> &#36;53 58&#47;11111 to <add>&#63;</add> I have added<lb/> &#36;6&#61; for 2 Bibles and enclose you<lb/> check for &#36;59 58&#47;11111 on Bk of New York&#44;<lb/> Will you please get for me a full<lb/> <sic>sett</sic> of your Books&#44; that is&#44; 1 <sic>sett</sic><lb/> Prayer Books and 1 <sic>sett</sic> Parasah Books&#44;<lb/> bound in Black and Gold&#44; same as the<lb/> <sic>setts</sic> I had for <persName>Emma</persName> and <persName>Charles</persName>.<lb/>  I want them for myself&#44; but no<lb/> name on them&#44; and am in no<lb/> hurry for them.  I read in Synagogue<lb/> on <date>Sabbath</date> and had quite a good<lb/> attendance.  I enclose you gold check for<lb/> 94 16&#47;11111 which I received today of <persName>Messrs<add>&#63;</add><lb/> Dovale Abr</persName>.  Please acknowledge receipt.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours vy truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName></p>
		</body>
